In the comma category, composition is defined as `⟨(f.1 ≫ f'.1, f.2 ≫ f'.2), ...⟩`, and `homF` extracts the first component `.1`. So `homF (f ≫ g)` gives `(f.val.1 ≫ g.val.1)` which is definitionally equal to `homF f ≫ homF g`.

```lean
